modules.description: Converts a string representation of time intervals into a structured duration type and formats a list of durations by preserving their original units in string form. Operates on custom duration values and lists of such values. Used to parse user input into standardized time units and generate consistent output for display or logging.

Records the startup time of modules at initialization and outputs the times in order before process exit. Operates on module initialization events and environment variables. Useful for profiling module load times during application startup.

Converts time interval strings into structured duration types and formats lists of durations while retaining their original units. Supports parsing user input and generating human-readable outputs. Operations include parsing, formatting, and list manipulation of duration values. Can transform "2h30m" into a duration and output ["1h", "30m"] from a list of durations.
